          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measurements of elemental fragmentation cross section",
                "for relativistic heavy ions using CR39 plastic nuclear",
                "track detectors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,NIM/B,29,675,1988",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,NIM/B,29,675,1988",
                    "doi": "10.1016/0168-583X(88)90475-2",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "NIM/B",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "29",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "675"
                      },
                      "date": 1988
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "C.Brechtmann",
                "W.Heinrich"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2GERUSI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  University of Siegen, Physics Department."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "1.  C(18)H(38)O is a wax-like alcohol called",
                "octadecanol which has a density of about 0.9 g/cm3.",
                "Target thickness = 2.007 g/cm2.",
                "2.  Carbon C target.  Target thickness = 2.314 g/cm2.",
                "3.    CR39 = C(12)H(18)O(7) is a polymer with a density",
                "of 1.32 g/cm3 and serves as detector and target.",
                "Target thickness = 2.216 g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CR39  plastic nuclear track detectors.  A typical",
                "Stack for a measurement of projectile fragmentation",
                "cross sections contains four CR39 foils each of 630 mum",
                "thickness upstream and downstream the target to",
                "identify the trajectories of the incoming and outgoing",
                "beam particles and projectile fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Invers geometry."
              ]
            }
          ],
